# Micro-SaaS Opportunity Engine Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your API keys

# =============================================================================
# REQUIRED: Bing Web Search API (for dynamic idea research)
# =============================================================================
# Get your key from: https://portal.azure.com
# Navigate to: Create Resource → AI + Machine Learning → Bing Search v7
# Copy Key 1 or Key 2 from the Keys and Endpoint section
BING_SEARCH_API_KEY=your_bing_search_key_here

# Optional: Custom Bing endpoint (defaults to standard v7.0 endpoint)
# BING_SEARCH_ENDPOINT=https://api.bing.microsoft.com/v7.0/search

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: SEO Metrics API (for search volume, keyword difficulty, trends)
# =============================================================================
# The system provides fallback metrics if these are not configured.
# To get real SEO data, you need to:
# 1. Choose a provider (DataForSEO, SEMRush, Ahrefs, etc.)
# 2. Build a proxy endpoint that returns this JSON format:
#    {
#      "search_volume": 1500,
#      "keyword_difficulty": 45,
#      "trend_direction": "upward"
#    }
# 3. Set the base URL and API key below

# SEO_API_BASE_URL=https://your-seo-proxy.com/metrics
# SEO_API_KEY=your_seo_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# NOTES
# =============================================================================
# - Without BING_SEARCH_API_KEY: Falls back to 5 curated ideas
# - Without SEO_API_*: Uses deterministic simulated metrics (fine for testing)
# - All APIs support rate limiting and graceful degradation
